# Web (`apps/web`)

## Stack

- **Next.js 16** (Turbopack in dev), **React 19**, Tailwind 4, `better-auth` client for session.
- **App Router** under `app/` — e.g. `/`, `/verify`, `/login`, `/dashboard/*`, `/bot/billing/success`.

## Env (see `apps/web/README.md`)

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` — browser + server API origin (no trailing slash).
- **`WEB_VERIFY_INTERNAL_SECRET`** — server-only; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`. Must match API server.
- `WEB_APP_URL` — canonical site URL in production (verify-lookup origin checks).
- Optional `API_BASE_URL` for server-side routes calling the API.

## UI

- Reuse **`SiteNav`**, existing spacing/typography, and design tokens (CSS variables + Tailwind arbitrary props like `border-(--border)`, `text-(--text-2)`).
- Dashboard shell, API key UI, settings/billing live under `components/dashboard/`.

## Patterns

- Public verify flow may use client components + server actions or route handlers; **`/api/verify-lookup`** proxies to backend with the internal secret — do not expose that secret to the client.
